Alembic migration guide for Guard Proxy backend.

Common commands (run from `src/backend/`):
- `uv run alembic upgrade head` — apply all pending migrations
- `uv run alembic downgrade -1` — roll back one migration
- `uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "message"` — generate a new migration
- `uv run alembic current` — show current revision
- `uv run alembic history --verbose` — show full migration history

Environment requirements:
- `DATABASE_URL` controls the migration target database.
- `JWT_SECRET_KEY` and `LOG_INGEST_SHARED_SECRET` must be set because application
  settings are imported by Alembic env during migration startup.

Offline SQL mode:
- `uv run alembic upgrade head --sql` emits SQL without opening a DB connection.
- Migrations must use dialect checks via `op.get_context().dialect.name` so they
  work in both online and offline mode.